    "descriptionModule": {
      "briefSummary": "To compare and evaluate the efficacy and safety of Candemore tab. versus Atacand tab. on blood pressure in patients with hypertension diagnosed congestive heart failure",
      "detailedDescription": "This is an open label, randomized, active drug comparative, Parallel group, Multi-center, phase IV study. Patients receive candemore tablet or atacand tablet. Initial dose is 4mg/day or 8mg/day. Every 2 weeks, patients take double dose if patients blood pressure is measured SBP ≥ 100mmHg and DBP \\> 60mmHg. Maximum dose is 16mg/day."
    },
